	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><span>When you are mounted on a creature, you fight as one. You gain the following benefits, unless you are incapacitated:</span></p><ul><li><p><span>The mount cannot take damage.</span></p><ul><li><p><span>All attacks against the mount target the rider instead, using the rider's Armor Class.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If the mount would otherwise take damage from something that doesn't target the rider, the rider takes the damage instead.</span></p></li></ul></li><li><p><span>The mount can otherwise be affected by terrain, spells, and abilities normally.</span></p></li><li><p><span>See Mounts for general mounted rules.</span></p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
